parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can lead to a loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
Fuel system failures can cause fuel leaks, fires, and spills, which can lead to accidents, injuries, and property damage.
symptoms: fuel flowing from one tank to another.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Acceleration due to Accelerator Pedal Mechanism Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the accelerator pedal mechanism can cause the vehicle to accelerate rapidly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without input from the driver
the accelerator pedal sticks or becomes stuck
the engine races or revs excessively
the throttle cable fails or breaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Ignition System Failure Causing Fuel Overflow and Backfire
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ignition system failure can cause an overflow of fuel into the exhaust system, leading to violent gas explosions (backfire) that can damage the exhaust system and potentially cause a fire, posing a risk to vehicle occupants and bystanders.
symptoms: loud noises from the exhaust system
and visible signs of fuel leakage or overflow.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure Causing Engine Fire
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failure can cause the engine to catch on fire, posing a significant risk to vehicle occupants and bystanders, as well as damage to the vehicle and surrounding property.
symptoms: smoke or flames are visible from the engine compartment
and the vehicle may experience electrical system malfunctions or warning lights.
